Have you ever wondered when you will have been married longer than not? This tool calculates that date for you!

Usage: longer --start <YYYY-MM-DD> --event <YYYY-MM-DD>

Options:
  -s, --start <YYYY-MM-DD>
          The start date, e.g. your birthday
          
          Format: YYYY-MM-DD (e.g., 1990-05-15)

  -e, --event <YYYY-MM-DD>
          The event to count as the midpoint, e.g. your wedding date
          
          Format: YYYY-MM-DD (e.g., 2015-08-20)

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')

  -V, --version
          Print version

EXAMPLES:
  longer --start 1990-05-15 --event 2015-08-20
  longer -s 1985-01-01 -e 2010-06-15

DATE FORMAT:
  All dates must be in YYYY-MM-DD format (ISO 8601)
